1
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:44,663
Mamma mia, I can't see anything!

2
00:01:45,004 --> 00:01:46,699
Where do I go now?

3
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:51,737
Madam is right. I should
buy myself some glasses...

4
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:56,547
but I look so awful in them,
and they make me look old!

5
00:01:58,918 --> 00:02:02,046
I'll have to ask Madam
for a little light.

6
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,428
How beautiful you are!

7
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:19,804
Do butterflies make you happy,
Medoro?

8
00:02:20,406 --> 00:02:21,430
Giving happiness...

9
00:02:21,541 --> 00:02:23,702
...is the most beautiful thing
you can do in this world.

10
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:24,799
Isn't that true?

11
00:02:24,944 --> 00:02:26,741
If something comes into the world...

12
00:02:26,846 --> 00:02:29,144
...and doesn't make our lives
more pleasant...

13
00:02:29,249 --> 00:02:31,274
...it might as well
not have been born at all!

14
00:02:33,887 --> 00:02:35,787
How long do butterflies live,
Medoro?

15
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:39,120
They say that a butterfly
knows no suffering.

16
00:02:39,592 --> 00:02:42,618
It lives one day in happiness
and then dies forever.

17
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:47,859
The only thing I don't like about
death is that you die for too long.

18
00:02:48,568 --> 00:02:49,796
It would be better
the other way around.

19
00:02:49,903 --> 00:02:50,892
What would that be?

20
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:56,135
If you died for just one day and
then lived forever in happiness.

21
00:02:57,377 --> 00:02:58,776
Have you ever died, Medoro?

22
00:02:58,912 --> 00:03:02,814
Oh, I still have to finish being born.

23
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:07,642
And anyway, time doesn't exist,
Madam Fairy.

24
00:03:07,754 --> 00:03:10,917
You're right, Medoro,
time doesn't exist.

25
00:03:11,491 --> 00:03:14,324
But let's go now.
It's getting late.

26
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:19,659
Yes. Well, I don't remember
the way very well.

27
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:22,731
You don't remember
or you can't see?

28
00:03:22,902 --> 00:03:25,302
This is the last time
I'll ask you, Madam Fairy...

29
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:29,136
...could we have
a thread more light?

30
00:03:29,776 --> 00:03:30,902
Just a little?

31
00:03:31,311 --> 00:03:32,744
All right, Medoro.

32
00:03:43,122 --> 00:03:45,420
Thank you, Madam Fairy.

33
00:03:46,459 --> 00:03:49,758
Let's go, little mice!

34
00:04:42,514 --> 00:04:45,483
Who is that?
- Get it! Catch it!

35
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:04,467
Here it comes again, over there!
We've got to catch it!

36
00:05:05,137 --> 00:05:06,570
Here it is!

37
00:05:17,182 --> 00:05:18,615
Who is that?
- My persimmons!

38
00:05:21,553 --> 00:05:24,147
Here it comes! I see it!
That's what it was!

39
00:05:24,256 --> 00:05:29,091
It's coming this way! Catch it!

40
00:05:31,897 --> 00:05:34,365
We've got to catch it!

41
00:05:34,466 --> 00:05:37,594
You rascal! You scoundrel!

42
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:43,708
Yes, you really are
a nice-looking frame!

43
00:05:43,809 --> 00:05:46,403
And now, you know what
I'm going to do?

44
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:49,538
I'm going to make you
a nice rose right here.

45
00:05:49,648 --> 00:05:52,139
You don't like the rose?
Oh, I knew it.

46
00:05:52,251 --> 00:05:53,479
Then we'll make a daisy!

47
00:05:56,221 --> 00:05:59,748
For heaven's sake, what's that?
Such bad manners!

48
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:03,728
Whoever you are,
you're really very rude.

49
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:07,464
What is this?

50
00:06:08,434 --> 00:06:12,530
Who does this belong to?

51
00:06:15,074 --> 00:06:18,339
Just look. What a lovely
piece of wood.

52
00:06:19,144 --> 00:06:21,374
Lovely, really lovely!

53
00:06:22,581 --> 00:06:24,446
I'll make a nice puppet...

54
00:06:26,485 --> 00:06:28,953
...one that can dance
and do flips...

55
00:06:30,255 --> 00:06:32,450
...well-mannered
and obedient, though.

56
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,493
Yes, let's start
working right away.

57
00:06:36,195 --> 00:06:38,390
I'll make the most beautiful
puppet in the world.

58
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:43,297
Come over here. You'll be
the staff of my old age.

59
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:51,441
Just look at what a lovely puppet
it's turning out to be.

60
00:06:52,311 --> 00:06:53,835
It's as if it were
making itself.

61
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:55,869
Am I hurting you?

62
00:06:58,383 --> 00:07:00,544
No, it's not a very hard job.

63
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,684
You see how lovely
you're turning out to be?

64
00:07:05,257 --> 00:07:07,054
Two nice big eyes...

65
00:07:07,726 --> 00:07:09,489
...some pretty black hair...

66
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:12,826
...and a cute little mouth
with a little tongue inside.

67
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:15,124
WOOD:. Will you let me try on your
yellow wig, Father, will you?

68
00:07:15,234 --> 00:07:17,464
I've told you a thousand times
to be quiet!

69
00:07:19,705 --> 00:07:22,003
I should have made
your tongue last!

70
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:26,067
And anyway, who told you
this is a wig?

71
00:07:28,046 --> 00:07:30,844
Can you really tell?
- You sure can.

72
00:07:30,949 --> 00:07:33,884
It's a big old yellow wig that
could make you die laughing.

73
00:07:33,986 --> 00:07:35,920
It looks like you have cornmeal
pudding on your head!

74
00:07:36,455 --> 00:07:37,888
Be quiet, you impertinent boy!

75
00:07:38,157 --> 00:07:42,218
Can you believe it? I haven't
even finished making you...

76
00:07:42,327 --> 00:07:44,090
...and already you're being
disrespectful to your father!

77
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:46,695
You're starting off badly,
my boy!

78
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:49,094
And just be quiet for a minute!

79
00:07:49,468 --> 00:07:50,730
All right, I'll be quiet.
I'll be quiet.

80
00:07:50,869 --> 00:07:54,464
I won't talk anymore because
my fath... What's the matter?

81
00:07:58,143 --> 00:07:59,474
Oh, blessed saint Anthony!

82
00:08:00,345 --> 00:08:01,573
He talks!

83
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,443
Yes, he talks!

84
00:08:04,449 --> 00:08:07,509
I really do think
I heard him talk!

85
00:08:08,487 --> 00:08:11,547
But let's try something.

86
00:08:14,393 --> 00:08:17,760
How are you?
- Fine, Geppetto. And you?

87
00:08:18,597 --> 00:08:20,827
Very well, very well, thank you.

88
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:24,162
Thank goodness
he doesn't talk.

89
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:28,998
Just what I was saying. How
could it be possible that a puppet...?

90
00:08:29,107 --> 00:08:30,540
Hey, Father, close that door.

91
00:08:30,642 --> 00:08:33,304
I'm all naked and there's
a draft in here, mamma mia!

92
00:08:34,813 --> 00:08:37,805
A puppet that knows
how to talk.

93
00:08:39,718 --> 00:08:43,552
Stop that, Father, you're
tickling me. No, no, stop that!

94
00:08:44,289 --> 00:08:46,484
Ladies and Gentlemen,
I present to you....

95
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,190
That's right.
What name shall I give you?

96
00:08:51,129 --> 00:08:54,189
Well, you came from pine wood.
I'll call you Pinocchio!

97
00:08:54,299 --> 00:08:56,995
Nice name, it appeals!
- What a lovely puppet you are!

98
00:08:57,102 --> 00:08:59,627
Your little shoes and little pants
are splendid.

99
00:08:59,738 --> 00:09:01,137
Now, the finishing touch.

100
00:09:01,573 --> 00:09:04,838
A hat made of bread crumbs,
painted by me!

101
00:09:06,211 --> 00:09:09,374
Wait!
- I like this one better!

102
00:09:10,516 --> 00:09:12,882
Father! There are
so many things in here!

103
00:09:13,252 --> 00:09:15,049
What's this? What's this called?

104
00:09:15,154 --> 00:09:16,781
Stop! Pinocchio, be careful!
Come here!

105
00:09:17,489 --> 00:09:20,390
Where are you going, Pinocchio?
Come here! My hair!

106
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:22,624
No one knows I wear a wig!

107
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:25,325
Be careful! You're going
to hurt yourself!

108
00:09:30,035 --> 00:09:32,503
Here's father's chair,
father's little table...

109
00:09:32,605 --> 00:09:34,072
...father's whatchamacallit!

110
00:09:35,107 --> 00:09:36,096
What do you see
out of that window?

111
00:09:36,275 --> 00:09:37,674
Can I take a look, yes or no?

112
00:09:37,776 --> 00:09:41,872
Oh, good God!
Where are you going? Get down!

113
00:09:42,147 --> 00:09:45,810
Careful, Father! Jump!
Bye, Father! See you later!

114
00:09:47,553 --> 00:09:50,113
I should have thought of this before.
Where are you going?

115
00:09:50,222 --> 00:09:52,554
It's so beautiful out there, Father!
Come and see! Bye!

116
00:09:52,658 --> 00:09:55,126
Don't go outside!
It's dangerous! Torna indietro!

117
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:10,809
What's that?
- Out of the way, puppet!

118
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:14,110
A puppet?
- What the heck is that?

119
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,850
Pinocchio!

120
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:21,613
Pinocchio!

121
00:10:22,221 --> 00:10:24,849
Pinocchio! Pinocchio!

122
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,423
Who is it?

123
00:10:42,675 --> 00:10:44,199
Get out of the way!
- Get out of the way!

124
00:10:53,218 --> 00:10:55,379
You're going to pay me
for that wine now!

125
00:11:00,626 --> 00:11:01,718
Got you!

126
00:11:04,096 --> 00:11:07,361
Got you! Finally!
Who does this puppet belong to?

127
00:11:07,966 --> 00:11:10,366
Let's figure out how much
there'll be to pay in damages!

128
00:11:10,469 --> 00:11:13,666
Who does this puppet belong to?

129
00:11:13,772 --> 00:11:16,138
It's mine! That wig is mine,
thank you! It's mine.

130
00:11:16,241 --> 00:11:18,436
If you only knew what I've
been through! There was a goose...!

131
00:11:18,544 --> 00:11:19,909
Quiet, puppet!

132
00:11:20,379 --> 00:11:22,142
Pinocchio, my son?!

133
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:25,215
A fine father you are! This puppet
is a real pain in the neck!

134
00:11:25,317 --> 00:11:26,306
What do you mean?

135
00:11:26,418 --> 00:11:28,716
I struggled so hard to make him
into a respectable puppet!

136
00:11:28,887 --> 00:11:32,584
Respectable? He's turned the whole
city upside down! It's your fault!

137
00:11:33,659 --> 00:11:35,126
He escaped from the house
before I even knew it.

138
00:11:35,227 --> 00:11:37,320
That's bad!
You have to be more careful!

139
00:11:37,429 --> 00:11:39,624
Only an idiot lets a puppet
escape from right under his nose!

140
00:11:40,566 --> 00:11:42,796
Now this one's coming
to jail with us. Let's go!

141
00:11:43,268 --> 00:11:47,500
Who's he?
- My son, where are you going?

142
00:11:47,673 --> 00:11:49,868
No, you don't!
Are you trying to escape, too?

143
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:53,143
You come with us!
You've got some damages to pay...

144
00:11:53,245 --> 00:11:55,509
...or else there's no avoiding
a night in jail for you. Let's go!

145
00:11:55,614 --> 00:11:56,979
Wretched boy!

146
00:11:57,783 --> 00:12:00,149
A little bird! Hey, I see you!

147
00:12:00,786 --> 00:12:04,119
Come here! Come here!
There are so many of them!

148
00:12:04,757 --> 00:12:06,782
Here's a nest! A nest!

149
00:12:06,992 --> 00:12:08,016
It's empty!

150
00:12:08,127 --> 00:12:09,424
A squirrel!

151
00:12:09,928 --> 00:12:12,988
It's so wonderful to be in
the world! This is really the life!

152
00:12:20,706 --> 00:12:22,970
I'm going to warm myself up
a little. It's freezing.

153
00:12:24,009 --> 00:12:26,068
What a great day I've had!

154
00:12:26,578 --> 00:12:29,479
And now I'm so hungry,
I could eat the whole house up!

155
00:12:30,315 --> 00:12:31,748
There must be some place
where my father...

156
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:33,043
Pinocchio.
- What's that?

157
00:12:33,818 --> 00:12:37,049
It is I, Pinocchio,
the Talking Cricket!

158
00:12:37,956 --> 00:12:39,856
No! A talking cricket?

159
00:12:40,225 --> 00:12:41,283
Cricket, you don't
by any chance know...

160
00:12:41,393 --> 00:12:42,519
...where my father keeps the cakes,
do you?

161
00:12:43,094 --> 00:12:46,461
Woe to those children who rebel
against their parents...

162
00:12:46,564 --> 00:12:47,963
...and run away from home.

163
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,691
They will never come
to any good in this world!

164
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:54,263
You're not talking to me, are you?
- Yes, I am.

165
00:12:54,639 --> 00:12:57,699
Woe to you!
- Cricket, I'm getting out of here!

166
00:12:58,109 --> 00:13:01,169
Because if I stay, I'll have to do
what every other child does.

167
00:13:01,579 --> 00:13:03,046
I mean, I'll have to go to school
and to study...

168
00:13:03,148 --> 00:13:06,140
...and I don't have the slightest
desire to study! I just don't like it!

169
00:13:06,685 --> 00:13:07,947
Poor little fool!

170
00:13:08,353 --> 00:13:09,843
You should know that if you do that...

171
00:13:10,188 --> 00:13:12,213
...you'll become a fine jackass...

172
00:13:12,724 --> 00:13:14,954
...and everyone will laugh at you.

173
00:13:15,393 --> 00:13:17,190
Hey, Cricket, why don't you
shut up for a minute?

174
00:13:17,295 --> 00:13:18,523
You've got an annoying voice...

175
00:13:19,164 --> 00:13:22,395
...and I really can't stand
to listen to it! It's really annoying!

176
00:13:22,634 --> 00:13:25,535
Well, if you don't want to go
to school, at least go to work.

177
00:13:26,104 --> 00:13:27,731
To work? Me?

178
00:13:28,073 --> 00:13:30,303
That's right! There must be
some job that you like.

179
00:13:30,775 --> 00:13:35,178
Yes, there is one that I like.
There's one that I like a lot.

180
00:13:35,814 --> 00:13:37,805
That's a good boy, Pinocchio.
You see?

181
00:13:38,249 --> 00:13:41,548
And what is this job?
- Eating, drinking...

182
00:13:41,653 --> 00:13:43,018
...sleeping, having fun...

183
00:13:43,121 --> 00:13:45,419
...doing whatever I like
from morning till night!

184
00:13:46,658 --> 00:13:50,594
You're really a puppet,
and you'll always be a puppet!

185
00:13:51,096 --> 00:13:53,894
And you're a bad-luck cricket, and
you'll always be a bad-luck cricket!

186
00:13:54,065 --> 00:13:56,863
For your information, dear
Pinocchio, those like you...

187
00:13:57,435 --> 00:14:01,337
...always end up either in jail
or at the hospital.

188
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:05,937
You're really a nasty
bad-luck cricket! You really are!

189
00:14:07,712 --> 00:14:10,408
Those like me end up in jail
or in the hospital, do they?

190
00:14:12,183 --> 00:14:14,014
And those like you...

191
00:14:14,119 --> 00:14:16,314
...you know where
they end up, Cricket?

192
00:14:16,821 --> 00:14:17,810
Where, Pinocchio?

193
00:14:18,156 --> 00:14:19,589
In the cemetery!

194
00:14:19,991 --> 00:14:21,652
Got you! Got you!

195
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:24,627
Hey, Pinocchio, what are you
doing with that hammer? Stop that!

196
00:14:24,729 --> 00:14:27,254
Got you! Got you! Got you!

197
00:14:32,837 --> 00:14:33,826
Where are you?

198
00:14:34,739 --> 00:14:37,606
I was joking. I didn't
really want to hurt you.

199
00:14:39,144 --> 00:14:42,409
Where are you, little Cricket?
- All right, I'll trust you.

200
00:14:43,648 --> 00:14:45,445
Can I really trust you?
- I can't hear anything.

201
00:14:46,084 --> 00:14:48,382
There's an echo over there
where you're talking.

202
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:51,582
Couldn't you come a little closer?
- Where?

203
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:56,585
Well, for example, here!
Right here where I'm pointing.

204
00:14:57,162 --> 00:14:59,392
That way we can talk.
- I'm coming, Pinocchio.

205
00:15:00,165 --> 00:15:03,362
I'm coming, for I have
a great truth to tell you.

206
00:15:04,536 --> 00:15:06,629
Those like you...
- Got you!

207
00:15:07,639 --> 00:15:11,439
You fell for it! I'll teach you,
with your annoying voice...

208
00:15:11,543 --> 00:15:12,908
I can't stand you!

209
00:15:13,912 --> 00:15:16,176
Cricket, where are you?

210
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:19,676
I don't feel like playing anymore!

211
00:15:19,784 --> 00:15:22,651
I'm starving, I'm tired,
I'm dying for some sleep...

212
00:15:22,754 --> 00:15:24,449
...I'm freezing, I'm starving.

213
00:15:24,556 --> 00:15:26,023
Cricket, I'm starving!

214
00:15:26,124 --> 00:15:30,151
What a horrible town!
What a horrible town!

215
00:15:31,262 --> 00:15:33,560
What a horrible town!

216
00:15:49,414 --> 00:15:50,938
Oh, God!

217
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:57,820
What is it? Father!
Dear Father!

218
00:15:58,289 --> 00:16:01,383
My dear little Pinocchio,
you were burning to pieces!

219
00:16:02,393 --> 00:16:05,851
If you only knew what I've been
through! I won't forget until I die.

220
00:16:06,030 --> 00:16:07,088
What happened, Pinocchio?

221
00:16:07,432 --> 00:16:09,195
It was raining. It was snowing.

222
00:16:09,534 --> 00:16:12,401
And you weren't there. I was
so hungry! Then the Cricket said:

223
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:14,597
"You deserve it. It serves you
right. You've been a bad boy!"

224
00:16:15,039 --> 00:16:17,269
And you know what I did?
I hit him with a hammer!

225
00:16:17,442 --> 00:16:19,069
I did the right thing.
I said, "I'll teach you."

226
00:16:19,477 --> 00:16:22,275
At a certain point, I was tired,
I was hungry, I was sleepy.

227
00:16:23,081 --> 00:16:26,346
And you weren't there,
do you understand?

228
00:16:26,451 --> 00:16:30,217
Then I sat near the fire to get
warm, and the fire burned me.

229
00:16:30,688 --> 00:16:31,985
Now I'm just
as hungry as ever...

230
00:16:32,223 --> 00:16:35,681
...and I don't have my little
suit of clothes anymore.

231
00:16:36,427 --> 00:16:38,952
Would you make me
a brand-new suit, Father?

232
00:16:40,098 --> 00:16:41,690
Why should I make you
another one?

233
00:16:42,433 --> 00:16:45,402
So that you can run away again
and get me sent back to jail?

234
00:16:47,105 --> 00:16:50,199
I promise you that
from now on I'll be good.

235
00:16:50,675 --> 00:16:52,370
I'll go to school,
and I'll distinguish myself!

236
00:16:54,412 --> 00:16:55,504
Is that a promise?

237
00:16:56,381 --> 00:16:58,576
The promise of all promises.
No joke.

238
00:16:58,683 --> 00:17:01,880
I promise you with all my heart!
- Good boy, my son.

